'
                '.*?' |    # single quoted strings or
                ".*?" |    # double quoted strings or
                \w+   |    # identifier
                \S         # other characters
                '

u'
    ::(?=[^=])|            # two :: (but NOT ::=)
    :[a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9]+| # :foo
    `|                     # ` (seldom used by itself)
    (?<!\.)\.\.[ \t]*\w+:  # .. foo: (but NOT ... else:)
    '

'
                '.*?(?<!\\)' |    # single quoted strings or
                ".*?(?<!\\)" |    # double quoted strings or
                \w+          |    # identifier
                \S                # other characters
                '

(?x)
        # Tokenize the input into keyword, separator, noise
        ([a-zA-Z0-9_]+)         |   # A keyword is a alphanum word
        ( \. | \:\: | \-\> )    |   # These are the allowed separators
        (.)                         # If it doesn't fit, it's noise.
            # Matching a single noise char is enough, because it
            # is used to break the tokenization as soon as some noise
            # is found.
'gettys are handled by|inittab is no longer used when using systemd'
'Unlocking a non-locked lock|accessing an invalid lock|which did not acquire this lock'
\\`(Tr|IX)\\' not defined|No such file or directory|(can\\'t break|cannot adjust) line
'^No contacts detected on SIM to import$|^Imported one contact$|^Imported [0-9]+ contacts$'

'(?xms)
(?:\${(\d+):(.*?)})|   # A simple tabstop with default value
(?:\$(\d+))           # A mirror or a tabstop without default value.
'

'(?x)
        \\.           |  # Backslashed character
        \(\?P<[^>]*>  |  # Named group
        \(\?          |  # Extension group
        \(               # Grouping parenthesis'

'
        # Include these so we can skip them:
        (?P<COMMENT>        <!--.*?-->                          )|
        (?P<CDATA>          <![CDATA[.*?]]>                     )|
        (?P<PI>             <\?.*?\?>                           )|
        (?P<DOCTYPE>        <!DOCTYPE\s+[^\[]*(\[[^\]]*])?\s*>  )|
        # These are the ones we actually care about:
        (?P<EMPTY_ELT_TAG>  <\s*[^>/\?!\s][^>]*/\s*>            )|
        (?P<START_TAG>      <\s*[^>/\?!\s][^>]*>                )|
        (?P<END_TAG>        <\s*/[^>/\?!\s][^>]*>               )'
